com.kuka.device.common

Class JointPosition

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.device.common.JointPosition

  • public final class JointPosition
extends Object
    Defines a joint position with arbitrary joint values in radians.

    This class is immutable. To create new instances of the class using the values of the existing joint position please use JointPositionBuilder

      • isNearlyEqual

        public boolean isNearlyEqual(JointPosition other)
        Returns true if the two joint positions are nearly equal.

        Equivalent to the call of isNearlyEqual(JointPosition, double) with default value of the epsilon parameter set to EPSILON

        Parameters:
        other - the other joint values to compare to this one.
        Returns:
        true, if nearly equal

      • isNearlyEqual

        public boolean isNearlyEqual(JointPosition other,
                             double epsilon)
        Returns true if the two joint positions are nearly equal.

        Every joint value is compared to the respective joint value of the other object with respect to the given epsilon.

        Parameters:
        other - the other joint values to compare to this one.
        epsilon - Epsilon value.
        Returns:
        true, if nearly equal.
